main event: A radar object was tracked for 12 minutes over Gransmere, N.J. on November 6, 1957.
interesting points: The object appeared as a vapor trail on the radar, with a size of a dime.
The object was lost on radar due to target fading, and its true nature remains unknown.
The report concludes that the object was possibly a balloon, but there was insufficient data for a full evaluation.
The sighting was a ground-radar observation, rather than a visual sighting.
sighted object: radar object with a vapor trail
